def: Having power to renew; tending to reproduce; regenerating. G.S. Faber.
In the innermost place. [R.]His ebon cross worn innermostly. Mrs. Browning.
The rank or position of a lady; -- given as a title (precededby her or your.)Your ladyship shall observe their gravity. B. Jonson.
The European green woodpecker. See Yaffle.
Toughtless; inconsiderate. [R.] Milton.Men are careless and incogitant. J. Goodman.
An apparatus for depositing and consolidating concrete underwater, essentially a tube of wood or sheet metal with a hooperliketop. It is usually handled by a crane.
The expected king and deliverer of the Hebrews; the Savior;Christ.And told them the Messiah now was born. Milton.
To snivel; to cry or whine. [Prov. Eng.] Grose.
To search after lodes. See Costeaning.
Of or pertaining to the day of birth, or its anniversary; as,birthday gifts or festivities.
A bitter white crystalline alkaloid found in opium, possessingstrong narcotic properties, and much used as an anodyne; -- calledalso morphia, and morphina.
